🧠 Explanation & Clarity
Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System

This is a simple, clear explanation of how the entire system works end-to-end without technical overload.

1. What this system is (in simple terms)

It is a system that automatically manages employees from the moment they join until they leave.

Instead of HR and IT doing everything manually, the system:

Creates employee accounts
Gives system access
Assigns tasks
Tracks progress
Removes access when they leave
Stores audit history
2. The Big Idea

Think of it like this:

Employee Joins → System Automatically Sets Everything Up → Employee Works → Employee Leaves → System Cleans Everything Securely
3. Two Main Processes
🟢 A. Onboarding (When someone joins)
What happens:
HR adds employee details
System automatically starts setup
IT tools are created (email, software access)
Manager approves if needed
Employee gets tasks and training
Employee becomes ACTIVE
Simple meaning:

👉 “New employee is automatically set up and ready to work”

🔴 B. Offboarding (When someone leaves)
What happens:
Employee exit is approved
System immediately removes access
Accounts are disabled
Company data is secured
Employee record is archived
Simple meaning:

👉 “Everything is safely shut down so nothing is left open”

4. Who uses the system
Role	What they do
HR	Adds and manages employees
IT	Gives system access
Manager	Approves actions
Employee	Completes onboarding tasks
Security	Ensures everything is safe
5. How the system works (simple flow)
HR Action
   ↓
System Detects Event
   ↓
Automation Starts
   ↓
